Went there for breakfast on a Saturday around 10. Pretty empty, wonderful atmosphere. The walls are sp pretry to stare at and the bar area is filled with fruits and juices. You can really tell the entire menu is made with love at this place. Great attitude too. Everyone was so sweet and nice. Right next door is one of my favorite bakeries too (bc they have vegan options) and I wish they would collaborate a little. Only downside I noticed was that the food was a little slow to come out but thats to be expected at a place like this. Its a great place to sit and chat and gossip during the weekend. As for the food itself, I have no complaints. I got the banana and nutella crepe and it was essentially a sugar explosion. Don't worry about the calories or sugar content. Just enjoy the food and tell yourself you'll go to the gym later. 5/5 would return.

Nezzled  in the heart of Pilsen, Creperia Nuevo Leon offers its customers a variety of  sweet & salty crepes, salads and smoothies, while enjoying the view of the vibrant community. Portions are huge, so be ready to share! Nice combination of flavors, attentive staff and relaxed atmosphere. While the weather permits sit at the patio and take some snaps of one of Chicago’s Most Endangered Building's, "St. Adalberto's Catholic Church".
